  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 70c970a7d9f7d414994564bd048e8a6d, type: 3}
  m_Name: UFO_Credible_Family
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: KBTV.Runtime::KBTV.Dialogue.CallerDialogueTemplate
  Topic: {fileID: 0}
  Legitimacy: 2
  Priority: 2
  Length: 10
  IntroLines:
  - Text: Vern, my whole family saw it. My wife, my kids, my mother-in-law. We all
      saw the same thing.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We were having a barbecue in the backyard when it happened. Six of us,
      all looking at the same sky.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I never believed in this stuff before tonight. My nine-year-old asked me
      what it was. I didn't have an answer.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  DetailLines:
  - Text: Bright white light, bigger than any star. Hovered above the trees for maybe
      three minutes. Then it split into two.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: My daughter started crying. Not because she was scared - she said it was
      beautiful. Then it just... disappeared.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Complete silence in the neighborhood after. Like even the crickets stopped.
      Everyone just stood there.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  DefenseLines:
  - Text: Six people, Vern. Three generations. We all saw the exact same thing. You
      can't dismiss that.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'm an accountant. I deal in facts. What I saw tonight doesn't fit any
      fact I know.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  - Text: My kids don't lie to me. My wife doesn't lie to me. We all saw it. That's
      not a hallucination.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  AcceptanceLines:
  - Text: Thank you. We needed to hear that. The kids especially needed to know they're
      not crazy.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'm going to tell them what you said. It'll help them sleep tonight.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: My wife is nodding. She's listening too. We both feel better.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  ExtraDetailLines:
  - Text: My wife got fifteen seconds on her phone before it vanished. It's shaky,
      but you can clearly see it split in two.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The neighbor came over after. He saw it too from his porch. Asked if we
      knew what it was. We didn't.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: My mother-in-law is 72 and doesn't believe in anything supernatural. She's
      been quiet all night. Just... processing.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  ExtraDefenseLines: []
  ConclusionLines:
  - Text: Thanks Vern. I'm gonna go hug my kids now. Keep up the good work.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We'll never forget tonight. And we'll never stop looking up.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'll try to send you my wife's video. People should see it. Thank you.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
